* typical file layout
@code text
src/
  payload.config.ts
  collections/
    Pages.ts
    Posts.ts
    Media.ts
    Users.ts
  globals/
    Header.ts
    Footer.ts
  access/
    isAdmin.ts
    isLoggedIn.ts
    canReadPublished.ts
  hooks/
    revalidatePost.ts
    setPublishedAt.ts
  fields/
    slug.ts
    hero.ts
    seo.ts
  components/
    payload/
      CustomDashboard.tsx
app/
  (payload)/
    admin/
    api/
    graphql/
@end

* when to use what
- collection: repeated documents like posts, products, users, media
- global: singleton data like header, footer, site settings
- hooks: side effects and lifecycle logic
- access: authorization rules
- Local API: fastest server-side access inside app code

* search ideas
- search `CollectionConfig` for schema examples
- search `access:` for permission rules
- search `hooks:` for lifecycle behavior
- search `payload.find(` for Local API usage
